Average rate(O2_Uptake(Control)): Residual oxygen uptake rate in the presence of test compound, control condition
Standard error(O2_Uptake(Control)): Standard error of the mean of oxygen uptake measurement, control condition.
Student's t-test(O2_Uptake(Control)): p-value of comparison with internal control in oxygen uptake measurements, control condition
Outcome(O2_Uptake(Control)): Inhibitory activity on oxygen uptake, control condition. Compounds were considered active if p-value < 0.01.
Average rate(O2_Uptake(Treatment)): Residual oxygen uptake rate in the presence of test compound, azoxystrobin-treated. AOX-induced condition.
Standard error(O2_Uptake(Treatment)): Standard error of the mean of oxygen uptake measurement, azoxystrobin-treated. AOX-induced condition.
Student's t-test(O2_Uptake(Treatment)): p-value of comparison with internal control in oxygen uptake measurements, azoxystrobin-treated. AOX-induced condition.
Outcome(O2_Uptake(Treatment)): Inhibitory activity on oxygen uptake, azoxystrobin-treated. AOX-induced. Compounds were considered active if p-value < 0.01.
Average rate(Growth(Control)): Normalized maximal growth rate in the presence of test compound, control condition.
Standard error(Growth(Control)): Standard error of the mean of growth measurement, control condition.
Student's t-test(Growth(Control)): p-value of comparison with internal control in growth measurements, control condition
Outcome(Growth(Control)): Inhibitory activity on growth, control condition. Compounds were considered active if p-value < 0.05.
Average rate(Growth(Treatment)): Normalized maximal growth rate in the presence of test compound, azoxystrobin-treated. AOX-induced condition.
Standard error(Growth(Treatment)): Standard error of the mean of growth measurement, azoxystrobin-treated condition.
Student's t-test(Growth(Treatment)): p-value after comparison with internal control, azoxystrobin-treated. AOX-induced condition.
Outcome(Growth(Treatment)): Inhibitory activity on growth, azoxystrobin-treated. azoxystrobin-treated condition. Compounds were considered active if p-value < 0.05.
